px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>This is just basic, out o=
f the box ChatGPT. It is very careful to remind me that it is not a lawyer.=
 There are a bunch of companies working on building legal-specific AIs that=
 will do a much better and more tailored job than this. Like </span><a href=
=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/46125994-55fb-47ba-a23c-b6efe48a4851?j=3D=
eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" st=
yle=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">Harvey</a><span>, which=
 has signed deals with top law firms and PWC and was recently valued at $15=
0 million by Sequoia. And yet&#8230; a simple ChatGPT conversation was real=
ly easy, and free.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I probably wouldn&#8217;t spen=
d the legal fees to sue my neighbor over planting trees in my yard, but wou=
ld I file a complaint for free plus the cost of the filing fee? I bet a lot=
 of people would. Rich people sue each other over things all the time becau=
se the legal fees aren&#8217;t prohibitive to them, particularly in the con=
text of the sizes of the things they&#8217;re suing over. Now, average peop=
le will be able to sue each other more easily over much lower value issues.=
&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>To Sam&#8217;s point, this might actually </span>=
<em>increase</em><span> the demand for lawyers. My neighbor, John Doe, migh=
t pony up for a lawyer to defend himself. And this is just a simple, person=
al case &#8211; when businesses big and small sue each other over littler a=
nd littler things, or write more and more complex agreements, they may need=
 to employ both AI </span><em>and</em><span> more human lawyers to deal wit=
h all of it. This is particularly true if you view lawyers, like consultant=
s, as a kind of CYA expense.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; fo=
nt-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">You can apply a simi=
lar logic to any number of professions. Certainly, some jobs will be automa=
ted away, but I wonder how many professions will actually grow because of A=
I.&nbsp;</p><h3 class=3D"header-with-anchor-widget" style=3D"-moz-osx-font-=
smoothing: subpixel-antialiased; -webkit-font-smoothing: subpixel-antialias=
ed; color: #404040; font-family: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-system, Blink=
MacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Col=
or Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-we=
ight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0; position: relativ=
e;"><strong>Divinely Discontent Customers Will Always Want More and Better<=
/strong></h3><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Another way of looking at this idea is, confus=
ingly, a different kind of demand curve described by Eugene Wei in </span><=
em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/7603f9fc-894b-49e1-950b-b150c07=
54b83?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" r=
el=3D"" style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">Invisible Asy=
mptotes</a></em><span>: &#8220;We speak often of the economics concept of t=
he demand curve, but in product there is another form of demand curve, and =
that is the contour of the customers' demands of your product or service.&#=
8221; Wei quotes </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/6f0284a5-5=
f36-4235-95ea-9a709f8253b0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXep=
KbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: unde=
rline;">Jeff Bezos&#8217; 2017 letter to shareholders</a><span>:</span></p>=
<blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #67bdfc; margin: 20px 0; paddin=
g: 0;"><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>One thing I love about customers is=
 that they are divinely discontent. Their expectations are never static &#8=
211; they go up. It&#8217;s human nature.&nbsp;</em></p></blockquote><p sty=
le=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px =
0;">As supply or capacity increases, customers will simply demand more and =
better products. Latent demand grows over time, as consumers see what&#8217=
;s possible today and demand more and better tomorrow.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D=
"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">T=
his is apparent in the world of atoms, where induced demand was born. When =
we get cheaper energy, we simply demand more and better energy-consuming pr=
oducts. When we get more lanes, we simply demand more driving.&nbsp;</p><p =
style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;">I suspect the same will be true for intelligence.&nbsp;</p><p style=
=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">Will AI take lawyers&#8217; jobs, or will we simply sue each other more?&=
nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 20px 0;">Will it take designers&#8217; jobs, or will we demand be=
tter design?&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Will it take doctors&#8217; jobs, or will w=
e all demand our own concierge doctors?&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Will it take eng=
ineers&#8217; jobs, or will we demand more personalized and higher-quality =
software?</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Will it replace startups, or will we demand more div=
erse and better instantiations of founders&#8217; visions, faster?</p><p st=
yle=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;">Will it take writers&#8217; jobs, or will readers just demand higher-q=
uality, more well-researched, more original work?&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"colo=
r: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>=
On the surface, AI looks like an opportunity for humans to do the same work=
 with less effort, and that&#8217;s certainly one possibility. The past few=
 weeks&#8217; rise of AutoGPTs &#8211; agents like </span><a href=3D"https:=
//substack.com/redirect/c4729626-455c-4ada-ab8c-46143f1a32cd?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOX=
AwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"col=
or: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">Auto-GPT</a><span> and Yohei Naka=
jima&#8217;s </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/045c0a1d-ecd9-=
42fb-a046-6d818cca3eac?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqO=
sa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underlin=
e;">BabyAGI</a><span> that act as semi-autonomous workers &#8211; lend cred=
ence to this camp. Maybe we&#8217;ll all be the CEO of our own bot armies, =
directing them with the occasional prompt as we sip pina coladas on the bea=
ch. Maybe we&#8217;ll get a three-day workweek in the near future.&nbsp;</s=
pan></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;">Maybe. But I doubt it.</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; fon=
t-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I suspect that the in=
creased supply of work will induce demand for that very human skill of figu=
ring out just what we should be working on. It would be a tragic self-own i=
f we used our new superpowers to endlessly sue each other back and forth.&n=
bsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Will it force us to change </span><em>how</em><span=
> we work? Of course. Will it push us to </span><a href=3D"https://substack=
=2Ecom/redirect/cc36cbfe-b463-4e36-934=
a-ec7e7535b87c?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.g=
b8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #40404=
0; text-decoration: underline;">differentiate</a><span>? Absolutely.</span>=
</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;"><span>But that could be a wonderful opportunity. Instead of w=
orrying yourself into paralysis, digging your heels in to do more of the sa=
me thing, or planning your next lawsuit, I&#8217;d encourage you to take so=
me of your newfound free time to paint a vision of the future you want to b=
uild with </span><strong>superabundant intelligence</strong><span>, and the=
n get to work.</span></p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;"=
